The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                fficers of five police stations in Barrackpore have seized nearly 50kg of banned crackers from different areas in Titagarh and Barrackpore in a series of joint raids since Saturday. Cops said they would patrol the highways to stop members of clubs from forcibly collecting subscription from truck drivers.  Torture complaint: Tapas Saha, a state health department official, was arrested in his Kidderpore home on Monday for allegedly torturing his sister mentally and physically over the past few months. Shipra Saha, a 58-year-old spinster who lives with her brother, lodged a complaint against him and his family members late on Sunday.  Factory fire: A fire broke out in a hosiery factory on Royd Street in Howrah around 5.30pm on Monday. The factory had been gutted in a fire on October 29. Four tenders took an hour to douse the flames. Fire brigade sources said Mondays fire had started when workers were removing burnt bundles of cloth from the factory. The smouldering bundles suddenly caught fire.  Suicide: Geeta Prasad, 22, was found hanging from the ceiling fan of her room in Salt Lake on Monday. Police said Prasad had a tiff with her husband on Sunday night. Bijay Choudhury, 48, a Shibpur resident, died after consuming poison on Monday. Police said Choudhury had a spat with his family members on Sunday.  Roadblock: Chhatra Parishad supporters blocked the MG Road-Kalakar Street crossing for 15 minutes around noon on Monday to protest the alleged failure of the health department to control malaria.  Plea: A three-member team of Trinamul Congress Chhatra Parishad on Monday urged the police commissioner to ensure that they were not harassed.                                                                                                                                                  
